properties.Name: ScheduledFlightLegPartyRelationshipType
properties.Description:
The nature of the relationship between party(s) associated and the Scheduled Flight Leg.

Ex:
- Ground Service Provider Party 
- Baggage Handling Service Provider Party
- Fueling Service Provider Party
- Maintenance Service Provider Party
- Control Operator Party 
- Grounding Handling Service Party
- Refueling Manager Party
- Pilot
- First Officer

where:

Refueling Operator: Refueling Handler staff trained to carry out the operations of aircraft refueling.
Ground handling service provider operator: staff belonging to a company that carries out ground handling services to the flight to be refueled
Control operator: Staff of the Airport Managing Company that may carry out supervision of the flight to be refueled.
Refueling Manager: person identified by the Carrier, which carries out coordination and monitoring activities to ensure compliance with procedures for refueling.
